ingredients:
2 pints (4 cups) cherry tomatoes, quartered  (I love a mix of red and yellow); ½ cup pitted Kalamata olives, thinly sliced; 3 tablespoons extra-virgin olive oil; 2 tablespoons lemon juice; 2 tablespoons oil-packed sun-dried tomatoes, rinsed and chopped; 2 cloves garlic, pressed or minced; 1 teaspoon balsamic vinegar; 10 twists of freshly ground black pepper; 
6 ounces feta cheese, crumbled (don’t buy pre-crumbled; buy a block of feta!)
; 
⅓ cup chopped fresh basil
; 
Accompaniments: Toasted crostini or pita wedges, crusty bread, pita chips or sturdy crackers…
